The Chinese mainland recorded 1,513 new confirmed COVID-19 cases on Tuesday, with 1,500 linked to local transmissions and 13 from overseas, according to data from the National Health Commission on Wednesday. A total of 26,525 new asymptomatic cases were also recorded on Tuesday, and 258,374 asymptomatic patients remain under medical observation. Confirmed cases on the Chinese mainland now total 168,362, with the death toll at 4,638. The latest tally of confirmed cases in the Hong Kong and Macao special administrative regions and Taiwan region is as follows: Hong Kong: 308,705 (60,660 recoveries, 8,886 deaths) Macao: 82 (82 recoveries) Taiwan: 28,666 (13,742 recoveries, 854 deaths)